title.narrative: 4.1 Strengthened government capacity to implement and monitor inclusive youth policies for Lebanese and Non-Lebanese youth.

description.narrative: Despite the struggles faced in the country at the governmental level, UNICEF continued to support government entities,including MEHE,MoSA,MoYS,MoL, and theMoA,to ensure marginalized youth;have increased;access;to;improved services through;implementing identified priorities in the TVET National Strategic Framework (TVET NSF). UNICEF also focused onaddressing protection concernsfor young people through the development and implementation of the National Protection Policy. Finally,theYouth-Focused Rapid Assessment (YFRA)improvedevidence generationthrough a national household survey targeting 15-24 yearsold. The three;levels crisis has nonetheless strained the government entities and affected many of the policy-level work of the section.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/12/2021
